Namibia to Build Second Water Plant in Uranium Region, Broadcaster Says

-- B y   C h a m w e   K a i r a
-- 
2011-03-03T09:12:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-03/namibia-to-build-second-water-plant-in-uranium-region-broadcaster-says.html
  Namibia  plans to spend 2 billion
Namibian dollars on a second desalination plant in the uranium-
producing Erongo region, the Namibian Broadcasting Corp.
reported, citing Andrew Ndishishi, the minister of agriculture,
water and forestry.  The first desalination plant was commissioned in April last
year, the broadcaster cited Ndishishi as saying. The government
also planned to spend 3 billion Namibian dollars on a dam near
the South African border, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Chamwe Kaira in  Windhoek  at 
 ckaira@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
